        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Linguist Martin Joos taught at the University of Toronto and the University of Wisconsin. Joos impacted the study of linguistics through his forty or more articles, reviews, and five books: 
                <emph render="italic">Middle High German Courtly Reader</emph>, 
                <emph render="italic">English Verb</emph>, 
                <emph render="italic">Five Clocks</emph>, 
                <emph render="italic">Acoustic Phonetics</emph>, and 
                <emph render="italic">Readings in Linguistics</emph>.</p>
        </bioghist>
